cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of inferring rich semantic descriptions of objects at part level, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a neural network for this task, which involves modeling of part state and pixel-wise annotation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions image captioning and robotic manipulation, which are related to natural language processing and robotics, respectively. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.RO (Robotics) are also likely categories.
